\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 2. Narrative, Characters & Flow\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Introduction (The Onboarding)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 When launching the app for the first time, players read a fast, 3-panel digital comic slide:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Panel 1:
\f0\b0  Igor (renamed 
\f1\b Meow-gor
\f0\b0 , a hefty cat) is staring intensely up at a plate of wet food on top of a towering refrigerator. A speech bubble reads: 
\f3\i "The rules say NO counters... but they never said anything about airspace."
\f0\i0 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Panel 2:
\f0\b0  Enter 
\f1\b Doc Frankie
\f0\b0 , a pocket-protector-wearing rat holding a tiny welding torch. Speech bubble: 
\f3\i "If we're going up, we're going up in style. Build me a frame, Meow-gor, and I'll wire the engines."
\f0\i0 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Panel 3:
\f0\b0  Quick gameplay diagram showing how to drag items onto a grid and synthesize them into wing mechanics.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 The Intermission (Between-Round Loop)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Every round concludes with a brief, randomized 2-panel comic critique between Meow-gor and Doc Frankie based entirely on the flight's telemetry results, immediately followed by the 
\f1\b Test Flight Simulation
\f0\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

