\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Phase 1: The Tactical Salvage & Grid Scavenger\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The player is presented with a messy kitchen countertop or pantry shelf. It is a 
\f1\b point-and-click hidden-object phase with a strict grid restriction.
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Constraint:
\f0\b0  You have a fixed $5 \\times 5$ grid inventory box.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Tactic:
\f0\b0  Items have varying sizes. A broom handle takes a $1 \\times 4$ line; a bottle cap takes a $1 \\times 1$ tile. You must rotate and arrange items to fit as many useful objects as possible.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Red Herrings (The Strategy Buffer):
\f0\b0  The countertop is intentionally cluttered with heavy, useless junk (e.g., an iron skillet, a soggy sponge, a crumpled napkin) that takes up massive grid space but has completely terrible stats. The player must think for a few seconds before blindly clicking an object: 
\f3\i "Do I really want to waste a $3 \\times 3$grid space on this heavy ceramic mug just because it's shiny, or should I hold out for a $1 \\times 2$ battery?"
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Phase 2: The Alchemist\'92s Kitchen (Synthesis)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Once the player fills their grid, they hit "Go to Workbench." They drop their items into category bins to reveal or execute a formula blueprint.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 4. The Content Matrix (Assets & Rarity)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To avoid animation bloat, components use a 
\f1\b Modular Asset System
\f0\b0 . Sprites use simple gray templates that are dynamically dynamically color-tinted and textured via code.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

